author: dvdmovie1
body:
"You think they won't realize how much money they can save on rent by just making everyone work from home permanently (essentially making employees shoulder their rent costs)?"

I agree with this and I think FIVN is something that will benefit in terms of call center employees working from home for the reasons you mention - now the employer isn't paying rent and utilities, the employee is.

"Malls/retail - no one is going to risk their life to go shopping when they can just order from home, COVID-19 is just accelerating the death of brick-and-mortar retail."

I don't think malls/retail are going away entirely but the gradual decline in a number of retail sectors that might have gone on for another few years is going to be compressed into a far shorter time period. The bigger retailers wind up bigger and stronger after this and I think you're going to see an increasing amount of retail stores be treated like hybrid store/"last mile fulfillment centers" - Target and Walmart are already doing this, to great success. I think ZBRA is something that may benefit from this (an increasing amount of "ship from store", "drive-up pick-up", etc) Target uses Zebra products for this, I believe Loews and others do, too.

author: GromGrommeta
body:
I mean look at Disney's ER for an example of why people would buy today. It's a pretty easy answer right? Either they hope to make money short-term or long-term.

Long-term you got some companies with a lot of good things going on trading at a discount. DIS is more than parks, and streaming is really what was moving the stock price even before the crisis. Good streaming results outweigh the known loss of park revenue, go figure.

Today I bought a bit of JPM, MCD and ZBRA, companies I already owned small amounts of before the crisis. Could they go lower? Sure, but I have absolute confidence in their continued relevance and success going forward.

author: natelrevoh
body: Liz Dierking and Jenny Andrews. They have a show called The LIZ & JNY. Part of the tastytrade network. They have some pretty innovative strategies. Jade lizards are their classic trade. They also have an interesting trade called a ZEBRA, which is a Zero Extrinsic Back RAtio. The concept is to place a back ratio without paying any Extrinsic value for the position, creating a nifty stock replacement strategy. I am no expert on these though, so you'll need to learn about them from the source. You can search for their content in the archives on tastytrade.
